es outside in GD.  You can see them a mile away if they have the bile.  I got 3 in a row.  Screw the caves.<br>
<br>
On 7th I have a pocket 54 war and another account with a 54 cleric.  Together we killed molkors and the lone sword fish to the right of the ent from CS.  Go in water under the tunnel and up on land at the bottom of the ramp that heads to tower with sirens.  The flat at the bottom of the ramp is SAFE.  So we kill the swordfish, it has tooth, I log war, log in wiz who is parked at safe ramp and loot tooth.  Easy as pie.  Use the clr's hammer pet and the 15dd reverse DS.  Buy the runed sea shell, sunstrike the ulthorks in EW.<br>
<br>
Only issue for me is the blood.  I don't want to spend 2k but Iceshard Keep (manor) is hard to solo.  Also my JC is only 169 need to get that up to... oh.... what do you think 180? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shafli>Shafli</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 88<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/19/02 12:03 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Well I'm only lvl 61 and...</span><hr size=1> I hate anything that has to do w/ tradeskills I think it's stupid that they put crap in the game that requires it. I will be purchasing ODS when I have the cash. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bjond>Bjond</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/24/02 7:01 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> For brewing, I'd highly recommend ..</span><hr size=1> .. using skull ale to skill up.  Obtain a skull from the undead cyclops in SK.  From EQ-Traders: Skull ale = vinegar + spices + short beer + cyclops skull.  Yield = 2 skull ales on success + cyclops skull (always).  Trivial = 151.<br>
<br>
You can easily buy all the parts cheaply from a single source and there are few components (less clicking). <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ayashii>Ayashii</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 33<br> <font color=#ffffff>(12/27/02 11:50 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: For brewing, I'd highly recommend ..</span><hr size=1> If you fail the skeleton ale, will you lose the undead cyc skull? <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://member.hkbn.net/~steph/Ayashii.gif" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
